In LaTeX, a table of contents can be generated automatically by using the `\tableofcontents` command, which is provided by the `toc` package. Here's an example of how to create a LaTeX document with a table of contents:
```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{toc}

\title{Example Document with Table of Contents}
\author{Your Name}
\date{\today}

\begin{document}

\maketitle

\tableofcontents

