In this example, the `toc` package is loaded with the `\usepackage{toc}` command. The `\tableofcontents` command is placed in the document where you want the table of contents to appear. The document is divided into sections and subsections using the `\section` and `\subsection` commands, respectively. These sections and subsections will be automatically included in the table of contents.

When you compile this LaTeX document, the table of contents will be generated automatically, listing all the sections and subsections along with their respective page numbers.

